abstract: WEEKLY REPORT OF DEATHS IN BROOKLYN. abstract: DEATH OF A PROMINENT NEW-HAMPSHIRE MAN.--We learn by a private telegraphic dispatch, that JOSEPH STEPHENS ABBOT, Esq.; of Concord, N. H., died of Cholera at New-York City last night. abstract: A fire broke out yesterday afternoon at 3 o'clock, in the stone yard of Messrs. HENDERSON  WILLSON, on Washington-street, between Wayne and Steuben-Streets, which was the most destructive that has ever occurred in Jersey City. The Fire Department were soon at work, but the fire spread with great rapidity, and was not got under until two entire blocks and the half of another bounded by Washington, Wayne, Steuben and Greene-streets, were destroyed.
